<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TimeML><TIMEX3 tid="t0" functionInDocument="CREATION_TIME"/>The Tokyo High Court <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">awarded</EVENT> 11.5 million yen  (110,000 dollars) <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE">Friday</TIMEX3> in compensation to the parents of a <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DURATION">13-year-old</TIMEX3> boy  who <EVENT eid="e2" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">committed</EVENT> suicide <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DATE">eight years ago</TIMEX3>, <EVENT eid="e3" class="REPORTING" tense="PRESPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">saying</EVENT> schoolyard bullying was the  cause.&#13;
The high court <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">increased</EVENT> the amount of compensation from four million yen  that the Tokyo metropolitan government, Nakano ward office, and parents of two  classmates who allegedly <EVENT eid="e5" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">bullied</EVENT> the boy, were <EVENT eid="e6" class="I_ACTION" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">ordered</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e7" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="INFINITIVE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">pay</EVENT> in the earlier  <EVENT eid="e8" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">ruling</EVENT>.&#13;
A Tokyo District Court ruling had <EVENT eid="e9" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="PERFECTIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT> in <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DATE">March 1991</TIMEX3> there was no "direct  link" between the suicide and the bullying. The parents of Hirofumi Shikagawa  <EVENT eid="e10" class="I_ACTION" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">appealed</EVENT> the <EVENT eid="e11" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">decision</EVENT>, <EVENT eid="e12" class="I_ACTION" tense="PRESPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">seeking</EVENT> 60 million yen in compensation.&#13;
However, presiding judge Nobuo Kikuchi <EVENT eid="e13" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT> <TIMEX3 tid="t5" type="DATE">Friday</TIMEX3> that the boy was  continuouslly <EVENT eid="e14" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">bullied</EVENT> at Nakano Fujimi junior high school in Tokyo's suburb of  Nakano for <TIMEX3 tid="t6" type="DURATION">five months</TIMEX3> before he <EVENT eid="e15" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">killed</EVENT> himself in <TIMEX3 tid="t7" type="DATE">February 1986</TIMEX3>.&#13;
"There is no doubt that bullying was the main <EVENT eid="e16" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">cause</EVENT> of the suicide," the  judge <EVENT eid="e17" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT>.&#13;
The school, <EVENT eid="e18" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">run</EVENT> by the Nakano ward office, <EVENT eid="e19" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">bears</EVENT> responsibility for the  boy's death because it did not <EVENT eid="e20" class="I_ACTION" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="NEG" modality="none">prevent</EVENT> the bullying even though teachers <EVENT eid="e21" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">knew</EVENT>  he had been <EVENT eid="e22" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="PERFECTIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">bullied</EVENT>, the judge <EVENT eid="e23" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT>.&#13;
Persecution among students is common in Japan's intensely competitive  schools, observers <EVENT eid="e24" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT>. Victims are usually shy or handicapped pupils.&#13;
In a suicide note, Hirofumi Shikagawa <EVENT eid="e25" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">wrote</EVENT> that the bullying was "hell on  earth." The school's authorities <EVENT eid="e26" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT> the pair <EVENT eid="e27" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">made</EVENT> him <EVENT eid="e28" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">dance</EVENT> in class with  his face <EVENT eid="e29" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PASTPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">painted</EVENT> and often <EVENT eid="e30" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">made</EVENT> him <EVENT eid="e31" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">run</EVENT> errands for them.&#13;
